08/07/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- The ten new members of government took their oath of office Monday (7 July) before Prime Minister Costas Simitis and President Costis Stefanopoulos. Addressing all cabinet members after the ceremony, Simitis stressed that he would tolerate no delays in implementing the government programme and would not hesitate to make further changes. He added that he would make the work of ministries more transparent, and make results more visible to the public.
In other news, Greek Defence Minister Yiannos Papantoniou met Monday with his Serbia-Montenegro counterpart, Boris Tadic. They discussed bilateral co-operation. (ANA, MPA - 07/07/03)
